Implements the feature requested in #264515 to allow users to create a new chat session by double-clicking on empty space in the Chat Sessions view, following the same UX pattern as the Explorer view.

## Changes

Added a double-click event handler to the Chat Sessions tree view that:
- Listens for `onMouseDblClick` events on empty space (`e.element === null`)
- Respects the `workbench.list.scrollByPage` configuration setting to avoid conflicts
- Executes the `workbench.action.openChat` command to create a new chat editor

## Implementation

The implementation follows the exact same pattern used in the Explorer view (lines 562-569 in `explorerView.ts`):

```typescript
// Register double-click event for creating new chat session on empty space
this._register(this.tree.onMouseDblClick(e => {
    // If empty space is clicked, and not scrolling by page enabled #173261
    const scrollingByPage = this.configurationService.getValue<boolean>('workbench.list.scrollByPage');
    if (e.element === null && !scrollingByPage) {
        // click in empty area -> create a new chat session
        this.commandService.executeCommand('workbench.action.openChat');
    }
}));
```

## User Experience

This change provides a more intuitive way for users to create new chat sessions:
- Before: Users had to locate and click the "+" button in the view title
- After: Users can simply double-click anywhere in the empty Chat Sessions view area

The behavior is consistent with the Explorer view where double-clicking empty space creates a new file, making it discoverable for users already familiar with that pattern.

Fixes #264515

